A  chieftain of the All Progressives Congress, APC,  in Delta state, Chief Julius Ogboru has floated a  group, Delta APC Action Movement within the party in the state. Speaking on the group, he said it will advance the fortunes of the party, adding that it will consolidate the party ahead of the next generation elections in the state in 2023. He said the movement is not a fall out of the leadership crisis rocking the party in the state, stressing that it has no relationship with the leadership crisis in the party. He expressed hope that the leadership crisis will be resolved amicably with the party coming out stronger. “The APC Action Movement is to strengthen the party. It’s also a way of mobilising for the party and consolidating it. It will be launched with spread across the state “, he said. Vanguard WHILE he ruled Edo State as Governor some years back, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, now the national chairman of All Progressives Congress, APC, did not camouflage his plan to take over the neighboring Delta State from People’s Democratic Party, PDP, which had held sway in the state since 2007. July 21, 2018 In "News" The leadership crisis rocking the Delta State Chapter of the All Progressive Congress, APC, took a worrisome dimension yesterday, as one of the factional Chairman of the party in the State Chief Cyril Ogodo said the party was not bound by the consent judgement procured by Ogboru/Agege faction of the… July 2, 2018 In "News" The All Progressives Congress, APC, has repeatedly stated its determination to upstage the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, in Delta State. However, that boast is itself challenged by the discord among different tendencies in the main opposition party in the state. February 6, 2018 In "News"